From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sr-0w <Sr-0w@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: hotdog: disable inherited APSS watchdog at entry

The downstream bridge can enter mainline while the SM8150 APSS watchdog state
is not owned by a bound Linux driver. Clear WDT0_EN while the MMU is still off
so a stale firmware/downstream timeout cannot reset a diagnostic kexec boot.

This is bring-up instrumentation. It must not be shipped as a generic arm64
change; the final implementation belongs in the Qualcomm watchdog handoff.
---
 arch/arm64/kernel/head.S | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
--- a/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
+++ b/arch/arm64/kernel/head.S
@@ -137,5 +137,13 @@ SYM_CODE_START(primary_entry)
 	 */
 	bl	__cpu_setup			// initialise processor
+	/*
+	 * Hotdog diagnostic handoff: prevent an inherited APSS watchdog from
+	 * expiring before the mainline Qualcomm watchdog driver can probe.
+	 */
+	movz	x9, #0x17c1, lsl #16		// APSS WDT: 0x17c10000
+	str	wzr, [x9, #0x08]		// WDT0_EN = 0
+	dsb	sy
+
 	b	__primary_switch
 SYM_CODE_END(primary_entry)
